The paper deals with the problem of computing the \textsc{Maxima} of a set of $n$ $d$-dimensional points, which is a fundamental problem in computational geometry. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The algorithm presented in the paper is sensitive to the structural entropy of the input set, which suggests that it may have applications in data structures and algorithms, hence cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely. The paper also mentions multivariate analysis, which suggests that it may have applications in cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The algorithm presented in the paper improves the running time for large classes of instances, which suggests that it may have applications in cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). Finally, the paper deals with high-dimensional data, which suggests that it may have applications in cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
